summary: An ordinance authorizing the dismissal of the suit instituted by the City of Seattle, for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of land and other property necessary for the laying off, opening, widening, extending and establishing of Spencer Street, et al, as provided for by Ordinance No. 42969, Cause No. 162238, of the Superior Court of the State of Washington, in and for King County, insofar as the same affects certain property.
